So this is the last picture of the series and you were maybe expecting a poetic caption under it but I want to spend this post to first say how grateful I am to have such amazing parents thanks to which this is the ninth time I visit Maldives. My dad took this pictures with a strong patience, listening to my suggestions on perspective, light and how to make a great difference with small details. It took me a while to pick the finals and share them, always in hope that you appreciate and recognise the engagement under every shot. It may surprise you that my dad wasn‚Äôt against some half naked poses, but this is the point of communication, fashion for those which are used to it has no moral rules, everyone has his own values or not, mine is personally to make everything elegant and not vulgar. I thaught my dad what‚Äôs the border between and he started enjoying the capacity to create something eye catching but not rude. This is what my job is focused on and I like to play with my body as much as I play with other models bodies. The making of a good picture it‚Äôs a perfect cocktail of self confidence and class. üåÖ .
